In this article, President Barack Obama issues a determination with respect to the Child Soldiers Prevention Act of 2008 (CSPA). He determines that it is in the national interest of the United States to waive the application of the prohibition in section 404(a) of the CSPA with respect to the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Nigeria, and Somalia. Additionally, he waives in part the application of the prohibition in section 404(a) of the CSPA with respect to South Sudan to allow for the provision of International Military Education and Training, and Peacekeeping Operations assistance. This determination is to be submitted to Congress and published in the Federal Register.